title: Pocket Notebooks
description: Pocket notebooks are ideal for taking notes on the move because they are compact and don't take up much space in your backpack or pocket. We should always have a notepad to scribble down ideas as they strike; we never know when that will be.

title: Spiral Notebook
description: The most popular type of paper notepad is the spiral notebook. Most users are students, and for a good reason. Cost-effectiveness is a major selling point. Sizes vary but typically have between 70 and 200 pages. The pages are frequently perforated, the books are wire bound, and three-hole punched.

title: Subject Notebooks
description: A subject notebook is a type of notebook that is common in most workplaces and classrooms as well as in the bags of most students. They are used in various academic and creative contexts, including jotting notes in meetings, drafting original works of art, and completing schoolwork.
